18/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The State Investigation and Protection Agency has arrested Suljo Karajic, 39, who was wanted for committing war crimes against Bosniak civilians in the Buzim and Velika Kladusa municipalities.
Prosecutors announced the arrest on Wednesday (October 17th), saying Karajic is suspected of war crimes between August 1994 and February 1995 when he served in the BiH Army.
In other news, Brcko Supervisor Raffi Gregorian met with Transparency International officials Srdjan Blagovcanin and Ljubinko Lekovic on Wednesday to discuss corruption issues and the mandate of Transparency International in BiH.
Gregorian gives the group high marks, especially in terms of its Civic Advocacy Partnership Programme, which addresses shortcomings of government administrators.
(SRNA, RTRS, OHR website, NTV Hayat, Dnevni Avaz - 17/10/07)
